# {Project Name}

## Project docs

Durable project knowledge lives in `docs/`. `docs/` is **not** auto-loaded — consult it by
relevance before working in an unfamiliar area; don't read it wholesale for trivial changes.

| Doc | Read when |
|-----|-----------|
| `docs/README.md` | Index of what's in `docs/` |
| `docs/architecture.md` | Touching structure, data flow, or how components wire together |
| `docs/decisions/` | Changing or questioning a past design decision (ADRs) |
| `docs/erd.md` | (DB projects) touching the schema — verify against migrations/models |

Precedence: code is the source of truth; `docs/` is a map that can go stale. Verify specifics
against the code before relying on them, and fix docs that contradict the code.
